HEADWORD: Ganza
<hw>Gan"za</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. <ets>gansa</ets>,
<ets>ganso</ets>, goose; of Gothic origin. See <er>Gannet</er>,
<er>Goose</er>.]</ety> <def>A kind of wild goose, by a flock of which a
virtuoso was fabled to be carried to the lunar world.</def> <altsp>[Also
<asp>gansa</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

